<dl id="n05038h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05038h">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05038h"> 38(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> acc. bish. of Dromore / Vat council as theolog.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Fr. Burke was now selected by the <mark>Bishop of Dromore to accompany him to the Vatican Council as his theologian</mark>. It was the first General Council held for three hundred years, and great interest grew round its solemn sittings. <small> William J. Fitz-Patrick, <a name="BURKE" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BURKE"><cite title="source">The Life of the Very Rev. Thomas N. Burke</cite></a>, (1885) [Chap. X, The Vatican Council] I, 321</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
